description:
AMI is seeking a full time Receptionistto join the teams in the Brick office locations. This is a great opportunity to join a growing outpatient Radiology practice!


AMI offers a generous compensation package including medical, prescription, dental, vision, paid time off (PTO), Paid Holidays, 401k and Profit Sharing, among other benefits!


The Receptionist is responsible for but not limited to:

* Greeting patients and visitors promptly upon arrival, courteously, compassionately and professionally;
* Answering incoming telephone calls, makes satisfactory disposition of the calls or transfers to appropriate party;
* Maintaining surveillance of all patients and visitors in the waiting area;
* Scheduling appointments, obtaining necessary information to input computer data;
* Performing clerical functions necessary to process and maintain all records associated with the Practice, ensuring accuracy and completeness;
* Accepts responsibility and accountability for work assignments ensuring that they are completed efficiently, effectively, accurately and timely as per policy and procedure;
* At all times, maintains focus on the needs of the patient and provides high quality care and service; and
* Performs other duties as required and assigned.

This full time, 40 hour per week position is based in the Brick & Brick Women's Center offices, with a work schedule of Monday-Friday 8am-4:30pm. The schedule includes rotating Saturdays every three weeks. Schedules are subject to change based on business needs.


Candidates must have a High School Diploma or equivalent. Intermediate computer skills are required. Must demonstrate excellent customer service practicesand have the ability to work in a fast-paced environment with minimal supervision. Previous experience in a medical office or hospital is strongly preferred.Candidates must have the flexibility to work days, evenings, and weekends and rotate to other AMI office locations in the region as needed.


AMI offers a generous compensation package including medical, prescription, dental, vision, flexible spending accounts, paid time off, 401k andprofit sharing and the opportunity to work in an exciting and progressive outpatient practice.


EOE

**Funding Analyst**


American Financial Resources, LLC (AFR), the corporate entity for AFR Wholesale (www.afrcorp.com) and eLEND (www.eLEND.com), is a national residential mortgage lender dedicated to helping homeowners, homebuyers, and mortgage professionals achieve their financing goals by delivering innovative mortgage solutions and an unparalleled customer experience.


AFR is not only one of the top lenders in the US, we are on the cutting edge of new technology and we are reshaping the lending landscape by providing our clients with new ways to simplify the mortgage process. **We are dedicated to the pursuit of growth and education and provide our employees with the tools they need to succeed. With defined career paths and robust training, AFR is your entry way to having a long term career with a solid company and many growth opportunities. Always seeking to add long term employees, AFR strives to provide the guidance to help you continue to grow with us.**

**Requirements & Preferred Qualifications**

* Proficient in Microsoft applications, including Outlook, Word and Excel;
* Willingness to learn quickly and take on tasks to support the team;
* Experience in a fast paced work environment, ability to multitask and strong written and oral communication skills;
* Must be able to work in a team setting and be detail oriented.

**Position Responsibilities**

* Verification of completed Settlement Agent applications for loan funding;
* Obtain review by necessary departments prior to loan funding;
* Note pending and completed tasks performed on each loan file;
* Verify settlement agent instructions via phone;
* Set up and submission of new wire instructions for previously approved settlement agents to warehouse banks for approval;
* Review funding documents including Closing Protection Letters (CPL's), wire instructions, errors and omissions and/or Fidelity Bond declaration pages;
* Post approved information in the database and loan file;
* Verify CPL's and insurance coverage by phone, website or email;
* Other duties as assigned.

* **This is a full-time position with a competitive salary and benefits package, including:**


	+ **Medical**
	+ **Dental**
	+ **Vision**
	+ **401K**
	+ **Paid Time Off**
	+ **Paid Holidays**
	+ **Monday through Friday work week**
	+ **Career Path opportunities**

**AFR is an Equal Opportunity Employer and is committed to employment diversity.**

**To apply please email****TalentManagement@afrcorp.com**
